# This config tells npm to use a custom registry for packages under the
# @manvithshetty507 scope instead of the default npm registry.
#
# Why this is done:
# In many projects (especially microservices), shared libraries are published
# to a specific registry such as a private npm registry or GitHub Packages.
# By mapping the scope (@manvithshetty507) to that registry, npm knows where
# to install or publish those scoped packages.
#
# Authentication to this registry is usually handled with a token (npm token
# or GitHub personal access token) stored in .npmrc or CI environment variables.
# This is commonly used in CI/CD pipelines to automatically publish or install
# private packages without interactive login.

# not actively implemented in project yet

# ----> @manvithshetty507:registry=https://<git link>/manvithshetty507
